title Supply-Chain Sustainability — Producer to Consumer
style wardley

// ------------------------------------------------------------------
// Anchors (multi-anchor: the sustainability system has distinct users)
// ------------------------------------------------------------------
anchor Consumer [0.98, 0.70]
anchor Producer [0.95, 0.55]
anchor Regulator [0.93, 0.40]
anchor Retailer [0.94, 0.65]

// ------------------------------------------------------------------
// Near-user layer: what each actor directly sees/interacts with
// ------------------------------------------------------------------
component Sustainability Rating (Consumer-Facing) [0.86, 0.55]
component Eco-Label / Certification Mark [0.84, 0.70]
component Storefront Distribution [0.82, 0.80]
component Online Distribution [0.80, 0.78]
component Coop / Community Distribution [0.78, 0.45]

// ------------------------------------------------------------------
// Regulatory apparatus (Regulator-facing, seen by Producer/Retailer)
// ------------------------------------------------------------------
component Laws [0.80, 0.35]
component Regulations [0.76, 0.45]
component Trade Agreements [0.72, 0.40]
component Sanctions [0.70, 0.35]
component Sustainability Guidelines [0.68, 0.30]
component Regulatory Bureaucracy [0.66, 0.55]

// ------------------------------------------------------------------
// Compliance layer (the apparatus that turns regs into visible signals)
// ------------------------------------------------------------------
component Certification Scheme [0.64, 0.60]
component Sustainability Disclosure (ESG reports) [0.62, 0.50]
component Third-Party Audit [0.60, 0.55]
component Continuous Monitoring [0.58, 0.45]

// ------------------------------------------------------------------
// Physical supply-chain flow — mid visibility
// ------------------------------------------------------------------
component Packaging [0.56, 0.70]
component Temperature / Freshness Handling [0.54, 0.60]
component Last-Mile Transportation [0.52, 0.75]
component Backhaul Transportation [0.44, 0.70]

// ------------------------------------------------------------------
// Manufacturing + sourcing layer
// ------------------------------------------------------------------
component Manufacturing [0.46, 0.65]
component Sourcing — Complex Products [0.38, 0.55]
component Sourcing — Raw Materials [0.32, 0.60]

// ------------------------------------------------------------------
// End-of-life layer — close to consumer in policy but deep in flow
// ------------------------------------------------------------------
component End-of-Life Reuse [0.40, 0.35]
component Waste Handling [0.30, 0.55]

// ------------------------------------------------------------------
// Enabling / knowledge layer (K-type): R&D, efficiency
// ------------------------------------------------------------------
component Resource Efficiency Practice [0.28, 0.45]
component Sustainability R&D [0.20, 0.20]
component Lifecycle Assessment Methodology [0.18, 0.35]
component Emissions Accounting Methodology [0.16, 0.45]

// ------------------------------------------------------------------
// Dependencies (a -> b means "a depends on b")
// ------------------------------------------------------------------

// Consumer flow
Consumer->Sustainability Rating (Consumer-Facing)
Consumer->Eco-Label / Certification Mark
Consumer->Storefront Distribution
Consumer->Online Distribution
Consumer->Coop / Community Distribution

// Retailer flow
Retailer->Storefront Distribution
Retailer->Online Distribution
Retailer->Coop / Community Distribution
Retailer->Eco-Label / Certification Mark
Retailer->Sustainability Disclosure (ESG reports)

// Distribution depends on the physical chain
Storefront Distribution->Last-Mile Transportation
Online Distribution->Last-Mile Transportation
Coop / Community Distribution->Last-Mile Transportation
Last-Mile Transportation->Backhaul Transportation
Last-Mile Transportation->Packaging
Last-Mile Transportation->Temperature / Freshness Handling
Backhaul Transportation->Manufacturing
Packaging->Manufacturing
Temperature / Freshness Handling->Manufacturing

// Producer flow
Producer->Manufacturing
Producer->Sustainability Disclosure (ESG reports)
Producer->Sourcing — Raw Materials
Producer->Sourcing — Complex Products

// Manufacturing depends on sourcing
Manufacturing->Sourcing — Raw Materials
Manufacturing->Sourcing — Complex Products

// Regulator flow — the apparatus
Regulator->Laws
Regulator->Regulations
Regulator->Trade Agreements
Regulator->Sanctions
Regulator->Sustainability Guidelines
Regulator->Regulatory Bureaucracy

// Regulations derive from laws; trade agreements sit alongside
Regulations->Laws
Trade Agreements->Laws
Sanctions->Laws
Sustainability Guidelines->Regulations
Regulatory Bureaucracy->Regulations

// Compliance turns regulation into visible artefacts
Eco-Label / Certification Mark->Certification Scheme
Sustainability Rating (Consumer-Facing)->Certification Scheme
Sustainability Rating (Consumer-Facing)->Sustainability Disclosure (ESG reports)
Certification Scheme->Third-Party Audit
Certification Scheme->Sustainability Guidelines
Sustainability Disclosure (ESG reports)->Third-Party Audit
Sustainability Disclosure (ESG reports)->Continuous Monitoring
Sustainability Disclosure (ESG reports)->Regulations
Third-Party Audit->Continuous Monitoring
Continuous Monitoring->Emissions Accounting Methodology

// End-of-life + waste close the loop
Consumer->End-of-Life Reuse
End-of-Life Reuse->Waste Handling
Waste Handling->Manufacturing
End-of-Life Reuse->Resource Efficiency Practice

// R&D / methodology underpins practice
Resource Efficiency Practice->Sustainability R&D
Resource Efficiency Practice->Lifecycle Assessment Methodology
Manufacturing->Resource Efficiency Practice
Sustainability R&D->Lifecycle Assessment Methodology
Sustainability Disclosure (ESG reports)->Emissions Accounting Methodology
Lifecycle Assessment Methodology->Sustainability R&D
Emissions Accounting Methodology->Lifecycle Assessment Methodology

// Sourcing is shaped by regulation (sanctions, trade agreements)
Sourcing — Raw Materials->Trade Agreements
Sourcing — Raw Materials->Sanctions
Sourcing — Complex Products->Trade Agreements

// ------------------------------------------------------------------
// Evolution movements (scenario, NOT forecast)
// ------------------------------------------------------------------
evolve Sustainability Rating (Consumer-Facing) 0.80
evolve Emissions Accounting Methodology 0.70
evolve Continuous Monitoring 0.70
evolve End-of-Life Reuse 0.55

// ------------------------------------------------------------------
// Strategic zones
// ------------------------------------------------------------------
note Open-market driven (consumer pull) [0.85, 0.80]
note Regulated zone [0.70, 0.35]
note R&D / differentiation zone [0.30, 0.15]
note Commodity logistics [0.45, 0.85]

// ------------------------------------------------------------------
// Inertia markers — "stuck" components with identified inertia form
// ------------------------------------------------------------------
component Legacy Packaging Lines [0.50, 0.55] inertia
component Established Audit Firms [0.55, 0.60] inertia
Packaging->Legacy Packaging Lines
Third-Party Audit->Established Audit Firms
